<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>BLESSING OF BAPTISMAL WATER</B></FONT></H2>
<H3><PRE>

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Em      Am                  B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.     Father, through sacramental signs,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       you work with unseen power
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                       Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       the wonders of salvation.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                            Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       In many ways through time,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       you have prepared the water, your creature,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       to be a rich symbol of baptism.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       At the very dawn of creation,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   Am              B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       your Spirit breathed on the waters,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       making them the wellspring of holiness.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       The waters of the great flood,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Am                  B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       you made a sign of baptism,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                        Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       so that today as then,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">           D                      C
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       the waters make an end of sin
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       and the beginning of a New Life.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Em                            D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       Through the waters of the Red Sea
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       you led Israel out of slavery,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                     D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       to be an image of God’s holy people
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                            Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       set free from sin by baptism.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       And in the fullness of time,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">            Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       your Son was baptized by John
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       in the waters of the Jordan
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       and anointed with the Holy Spirit.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       Lifted up upon the cross,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                        C               B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       blood and water flowed from His side.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">              Em           D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.     LIFTED UP UPON THE CROSS,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                         C              B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       BLOOD AND WATER FLOWED FROM HIS SIDE.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">            Em             D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.     And after His resurrection,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                    Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       He told His disciples:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               D                Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       “Go out, announce the Gospel to all the nations
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                           D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       baptizing them in the name of the Father
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   C                   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit.”

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">           Em                              D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.     BAPTIZING THEM IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   C                   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       AND OF THE SON AND OF THE HOLY SPIRIT.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.     Father, Father,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                     D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       look now with love upon your Church
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                       C                   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       and unseal for her the fountain of baptism.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">               Em           D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       By the power of the Spirit,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                  C
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       give to the water of this font
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                         B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       the grace of your Son.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">           Em                              D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       So that through the sacrament of baptism
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                    Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       the man created in your own likeness
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                        D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       may be cleansed from the blot of sin
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                       C
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       and be born again by water and Spirit
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       as a new creature.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Em              Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       Father, may descend upon these waters,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       by the virtue of your Son,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">            C                 B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       the power of the Holy Spirit,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">               Em                       D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       so that all who are buried with Christ
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                       Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       in the death of baptism
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                            D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       dead with Him, rise also with Him,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             C
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       rise also with Him,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       to a new and eternal life.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                  Em        D
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.     DEAD WITH HIM, RISE ALSO WITH HIM,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             C
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       RISE ALSO WITH HIM
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">       TO A NEW AND ETERNAL LIFE

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.     Through our Lord Jesus Christ.

